abstract.text: Processes and saves a full-quality Live Photo as the output of your editing session.

inlineContent.text: The photo editing output to receive the rendered Live Photo, created from the same
object you used to begin this Live Photo editing context.

if rendering succeeds; otherwise

. If rendering fails, this parameter contains an error object describing the failure.

Use this method when you have finished an editing session and need to provide rendered output in a
object. Unlike when rendering output for a photo or video asset, you don’t need to provide rendered output using the
property of the editing output object. Instead, create a
object using the
initializer, passing the same
object you used in the
initializer to start this Live Photo editing context. Then pass that editing output object to this method, and Photos renders the Live Photo and provides it to the editing output.
Don’t forget to describe your edits in a
object and provide that to the

property of your content editing output. Providing adjustment data allows your app (or photo editing extension) to non-destructively resume working with an edit later, whether on the same device or on another Mac or iOS device using iCloud Photo Library.
After this method’s completion handler signals successful rendering, you use the content editing output to complete the edit. In an app using the Photos framework, create a
object inside a
block, and set its
property to your editing output. In a photo editing extension running in the Photos app, your main view controller provides content editing output when requested by the
method.

abstract.text: Work with image and video assets that the Photos app manages, including those from iCloud Photos and Live Photos.
A description of the edits made to an asset’s photo, video, or Live Photo content, which allows your app to reconstruct or revert the effects of prior editing sessions.
A request to create, delete, change metadata for, or edit the content of a Photos asset, for use in a photo library change block.
The output of an asset content editing session.
A container that provides information about and access to the image, video, or Live Photo content of an asset to be edited.
A container to which you provide the results of editing the photo, video, or Live Photo content of a Photos asset.
An object describing the changes made to the asset.
Creates an editing output from the specified editing input.
The URL at which to write a file containing edited asset content.
An editing session for modifying the photo, video, and audio content of a Live Photo.
Aborts any Live Photo processing in progress.
Processes a Live Photo with your edits for viewing.
Processes and saves a full-quality Live Photo as the output of your editing session.
Keys for the
dictionary used with the methods listed in Processing an Editing Context’s Live Photo.
The signature for a block Photos calls to process Live Photo frames.
An object that manages access and changes to the user’s photo library.
Asks your extension for edited asset data to finish the editing session.
Type to represent a Boolean value.
Information about an error condition including a domain, a domain-specific error code, and application-specific information.
A Unicode string value that is a collection of characters.
A value type whose instances are either `true` or `false`.
The return type of functions that don’t explicitly specify a return type, that is, an empty tuple `()`.
A type representing an error value that can be thrown.
